text: Patrick Stephen Murphy (13 May 1889 – 1 May 1968) was an Irish politician. He was first elected to the lower house of the parliament of Ireland (Dáil Éireann) in 1932. He was a member of the Fianna Fáil political party. He was the member of parliament (Teachta Dála or TD) for the Cork East constituency. ==References== Category:1889 births Category:1968 deaths Category:Irish politicians
